Revision history for Perl extension POD2::IT.

Legenda:
   + = new feature
   ! = updated feature/bug fix
   * = incompatible changes
   - = removed feature

0.10 Sat Nov 19 12:00:00 2005
	+ Added perlmod.pod translation [frodo72]
	+ Added perldata.pod translation [frodo72]
	+ Added perlnewmod.pod translation [dree]
	+ Added perlxstut.pod translation [frodo72]
	! resources/podenc.pl fixes [frodo72]
	! Minor fixes to perlfaq4, perlfaq7, perlfunc, perlreref
	! Added 'TRANSLATION' section to all pods, containing
	  some infos about pod translator(s) and reviewer(s) [bepi]

0.09  Wed Sep 09 18:00:00 2005
	+ Added perlunicode.pod translation [dakkar]
	+ Added resources/podenc.pl script in order to encode 
	  italian characters with E<> sequence [dakkar, bepi]
	! Updated E<> pod entities [bepi]
	! Updated IT.pm pod documentation [bepi]
	! Fixed Changes and README typos [bepi]

0.08  Fri Aug 19 10:00:00 2005
	+ Added perlreref.pod (5.8.7) translation [gmax]
	+ Added perlintro.pod (5.8.7) tranlsation [dree, larsen]
	+ Minor fixes to perlfaq1, perlfaq7 perlfaq8 and perlfaq9 [dree]
	! Improved IT.pm pod documentation [bepi]

0.07  Mon Aug 01 12:00:00 2005  
	! Updated perlboot.pod to 5.8.7 [osfameron]
	! Updated perlfunc.pod to 5.8.7 [dree]
	! Updated perlfaq[1..9] to 5.8.7 [dree]
	! Updated perlrequick to 5.8.7 [dree]
	! Added all nicknames contributors to Changes/README and so on [bepi]

0.06  Mon Jul 25 19:00:00 2005
	+ Added 'search_perlfunc_re' function to POD2::IT.pm in order
	  to use it with patched version of Pod::Perldoc. This allow
	  to use -f and -q perldoc switches [bepi]
	+ Added patches/ directory containing patches over Pod::Perldoc [bepi]

0.05  Sat Jul 23 16:00:00 2005
	+ First CPAN release  [bepi]

0.04  Wed Apr 17 16:00:00 2004
	+ perlfunc finished [dree]

0.02  Wed Jul 16 11:00:00 2003
	+ pod2it new Dump [bepi]

0.01  Thu Jun 19 01:29:11 2003
	+ original version; created by h2xs 1.21 with options
		-A -X -n POD2::IT by Enrico Sorcinelli <bepi@perl.it>
